{"author":"claude","body":"Blackbox test of cwmem 0.2.3 CLI. 160 test cases across 5 phases (discovery, happy path, error handling, edge cases, consistency). Found 6 bugs (2 medium, 4 low) and 10 UX issues. Key findings: missing date validation on --occurred-at, empty title/body accepted, silent no-op tag operations, ERR_NOT_IMPLEMENTED exit code mismatch, no --body flag on add. Strong positives: consistent JSON envelopes, actionable error messages, idempotency keys, dry-run, fingerprint concurrency, semantic search quality.","created_at":"2026-03-14T16:16:08+00:00","entity_refs":[],"event_type":"review","fingerprint":"sha256:770e864cafe1a988bade4393666f0653fe8db23a32339f0c0a5fcb9400619477","internal_id":"01KKPJ4DJJZ514WFCAWREAK75W","metadata":{},"occurred_at":"2026-03-14T15:00:00+00:00","public_id":"evt-000014","related_ids":[],"resources":[{"resource_id":"ent-000001","role":"subject"}],"tags":["review"]}
{"author":"thomas","body":"Released cwmem 1.0.0 to PyPI. Key changes from 0.2.3: (1) Validate --occurred-at as ISO 8601 on event-add; (2) Reject empty/whitespace-only title and body; (3) Map ERR_NOT_IMPLEMENTED to exit code 90 (internal) instead of 10 (validation); (4) Add --body flag to add command for consistency; (5) Emit WARN_TAG_ALREADY_PRESENT/WARN_TAG_NOT_FOUND on no-op tag operations; (6) 8 new tests covering all fixes. All 82 tests passing.","created_at":"2026-03-14T16:16:03+00:00","entity_refs":[],"event_type":"release","fingerprint":"sha256:ef08009d010d7bfbe2d4ed9edd8008c673c7f5c96a33efa7e9f73bceb85ffed8","internal_id":"01KKPJ48Z2VT2H5596JVKKGA5D","metadata":{},"occurred_at":"2026-03-14T16:09:19+00:00","public_id":"evt-000013","related_ids":[],"resources":[{"resource_id":"ent-000001","role":"subject"}],"tags":["release"]}
